utable, `ConfigFactory` still sees zero `reference.conf` resources. I’m now inspecting the generated native-image configuration files to confirm how our metadata entry is being translated, because this looks like a registration-shape issue rather than a Pekko-specific one.\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-stream_2.13:1.1.5/metadata-fix/codex.log:109:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_60\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -c \\\"grep -RIn 'reachability-metadata' docs/metadata.md docs/tests.md docs/README.md 2>/dev/null\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"docs/metadata.md:22:- `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`\\ndocs/metadata.md:25:  single-file format of the vendored `reachability-metadata` schema. The legacy\\ndocs/metadata.md:33:  (`reachability-metadata`, `metadata-library-index`,\\ndocs/metadata.md:50:- **Conditional on `typeReached`, and nothing else.** Every reachability-metadata\\ndocs/metadata.md:60:  `reachability-metadata` and `metadata-library-index` schemas follow semver\\ndocs/metadata.md:63:  non-plugin formats), while a **major bump (e.g. `reachability-metadata` 1.2.0 →\\ndocs/metadata.md:80:`metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/reachability-metadata.json` and into the\\ndocs/metadata.md:82:`tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json`.\\ndocs/tests.md:18:- `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json`\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-stream_2.13:1.1.5/metadata-fix/codex.log:111:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_61\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -c \\\"grep -RIn 'resource-config.json' docs metadata forge tests src tck-build-logic 2>/dev/null | head -n 200\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"a.\\nforge/.claude/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:110:- Legacy config files such as `reflect-config.json` or `resource-config.json` are added.\\nforge/tests/test_metrics_paths.py:480:            with open(os.path.join(test_metadata_dir, \\\"resource-config.json\\\"), \\\"w\\\", encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\") as file:\\nforge/tests/test_metrics_paths.py:484:                \\\"tests/src/org.example/demo/1.0.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/resource-config.json\\\"\\nforge/tests/test_metrics_paths.py:489:                    \\\"tests/src/org.example/demo/1.0.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/resource-config.json\\\",\\nforge/utility_scripts/native_image_config_policy.py:18:        \\\"resource-config.json\\\",\\ntests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-daemon-embeddable/2.3.20/build.gradle:32:            new File(baseDir, \\\"resource-config.json\\\").text = '{ \\\"resources\\\": { \\\"includes\\\": [] } }\\\\n'\\ntests/src/io.smallrye/jandex-gizmo2/3.5.3/build.gradle:25:        new File(baseDir, \\\"resource-config.json\\\").text = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\ntests/src/net.java.dev.jna/jna/README.md:2:libraries to `resource-config.json`.\\ntests/src/com.google.javascript/closure-compiler-externs/v20150505/build.gradle:27:        new File(baseDir, \\\"resource-config.json\\\").text = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-stream_2.13:1.1.5/metadata-fix/codex.log:112:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_62\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"The repo docs mention both shipped metadata and test-local metadata under `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image`. I’m checking whether this fixture expects a mirrored test metadata file for the native test to see `reference.conf`, even though the library metadata directory is also on the configuration path.\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-stream_2.13:1.1.5/metadata-fix/codex.log:114:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_63\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -c \\\"sed -n '1,120p' docs/metadata.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# METADATA-suite: The `metadata/` suite\\n\\n[`metadata/`](../metadata) is the repository's product: the curated GraalVM\\nreachability metadata that native-build-tools resolves and passes to\\n`native-image`. Everything else in the repository exists to produce, validate,\\nor describe it. Its contract toward consumers is normative in\\n§FS-repository-functional-spec.4 (distribution and the native-build-tools\\ninterface); this document describes the suite's purpose and layout.\\n\\nThe metadata is purely additive — it only fills in registrations `native-image`\\nwould otherwise miss, and must never change how a consumer's code runs\\n(§FS-repository-functional-spec.3, §GRUND-repository-motivation).\\n\\n## 1. Layout\\n\\n- `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json` — one per supported artifact: a\\n  JSON array recording, per metadata version, the `tested-versions`,\\n  `allowed-packages`, the source/test/documentation/repository URLs, and optional\\n  `default-for`, `latest`, `override`, `requires`, `test-version`,\\n  `skipped-versions`, and `language`. This is how native-build-tools selects a\\n  metadata version for a dependency (§FS-repository-functional-spec.4).\\n- `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`\\n  — the only file `native-image` loads. It carries `reflection`, `jni`,\\n  `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls` entries in the\\n  single-file format of the vendored `reachability-metadata` schema. The legacy\\n  split-config files (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`,\\n  `resource-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`) are\\n  never used here.\\n- `metadata/library-and-framework-list.json` — the master list of every\\n  supported library with its `test_level`, driving the\\n  libraries-and-frameworks page.\\n- [`metadata/schemas/`](../metadata/schemas) — vendored JSON schemas\\n  (`reachability-metadata`, `metadata-library-index`,\\n  `library-and-framework-list`) used for offline validation; also packaged into\\n  the release.\\n\\n### `not-for-native-image` index entries\\n\\nAn `index.json` may instead be a single-element array whose one entry sets\\n`not-for-native-image: true`, with a required `reason` and an optional\\n`replacement`. This marks an artifact that is intentionally **not** a\\nnative-image metadata target — a Scala.js artifact, a pure test framework, an\\nartifact superseded by another coordinate — so the absence of any\\n`metadata-version` directory is a recorded decision rather than a missing-support\\ngap. The entry carries no `tested-versions` or `allowed-packages`, and\\nnative-build-tools loads no metadata for such a coordinate.\\n\\n## 2. Invariants\\n\\n- **Conditional on `typeReached`, and nothing else.** Every reachability-metadata\\n  entry is gated on a `condition` whose only key is `typeReached`.\\n  `typeReached` is the sole condition key the vendored schema accepts; no other\\n  condition form — including the older `typeReachable` — is valid, and\\n  `checkMetadataFiles` rejects any entry that uses one. The reached type must lie\\n  inside the artifact's `allowed-packages`, and no entry may target a test-only\\n  type (§FS-repository-functional-spec.5.1). No build-time-initialization\\n  directives, library patches, or `Feature` classes ship here\\n  (§FS-repository-functional-spec.3).\\n- **Schema semver tracks the native-build-tools contract.** The\\n  `reachability-metadata` and `metadata-library-index` schemas follow semver\\n  against that contract: **minor and patch bumps stay backward-compatible** with\\n  already-released native-build-tools (they add optional fields or auxiliary,\\n  non-plugin formats), while a **major bump (e.g. `reachability-metadata` 1.2.0 →\\n  2.0.0) represents a required change in native-build-tools** and is released in\\n  lockstep with a plugin update — it is not an additive change older plugins\\n  silently absorb (§FS-repository-functional-spec.4).\\n- **Schema-valid and sorted.** JSON validates against its vendored schema and is\\n  key-sorted; `index.json` integrity and entry validity are enforced by\\n  `validateIndexFiles` and `checkMetadataFiles` (§TCK-test-harness.2) and the\\n  matching CI workflows (§CI-repository-ci).\\n\\n### Test-only metadata is kept out of the shipped metadata\\n\\nTests routinely need reachability metadata for their *own* helper types — the\\ntest classes, fixtures, and resources that exercise the library — but those\\nentries must never reach a consumer (§FS-repository-functional-spec.5.1). The\\nharness `splitTestOnlyMetadata` task (§TCK-test-harness.5) maintains that\\nseparation: any entry whose `type` or `condition.typeReached` names a test\\npackage, or whose resource is a test resource, is moved out of the library's\\n`metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/reachability-metadata.json` and into the\\ntest project's\\n`tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json`.\\nThe shipped metadata therefore stays free of test-only types, while the test\\nnative image still loads everything it needs from its own resources.\\n\\n## 3. Provenance\\n\\nNo file here is hand-trusted: each metadata entry is justified by a test in the\\n`tests/` suite (§TESTS-suite, §GOAL-tested-metadata) and is added or updated only\\nthrough the harness authoring tasks (§TCK-test-harness.5) by a human contributor\\nor by Forge (§forge/FS-forge-functional-spec). Coverage grows without weakening\\nwhat already ships (§GOAL-protect-shipped-metadata).\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-stream_2.13:1.1.5/metadata-fix/codex.log:117:{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_65\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -c \\\"grep -RIn 'reference.conf' tests/src/*/*/*/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json 2>/dev/null | head -n 80\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-stream_2.13:1.1.5/metadata-fix/codex.log:118:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_65\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -c \\\"grep -RIn 'reference.conf' tests/src/*/*/*/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json 2>/dev/null | head -n 80\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-stream_2.13:1.1.5/metadata-fix/codex.log:119:{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_66\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -c \\\"grep -RIn 'src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json' tests/src | head -n 80\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-stream_2.13:1.1.5/metadata-fix/codex.log:120:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_66\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -c \\\"grep -RIn 'src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json' tests/src | head -n 80\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-stream_2.13:1.1.5/metadata-fix/codex.log:121:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_67\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"This has moved past the obvious fix, so I’m checking local git history for prior Pekko or config-resource fixes in this repository. If there’s an existing pattern or reverted change, that’s the fastest way to make this correct instead of guessing at native-image resource semantics.\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-stream_2.13:1.1.5/metadata-fix/codex.log:145:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\